The paper proposes a new architecture for learning effective representations of large graphs, which is a common problem in machine learning and artificial intelligence. The paper also mentions the use of neural networks and kernel methods, which are common techniques in the subfields of machine learning and artificial intelligence. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), and cs.SD (Software Engineering).
